## GUIDE Mode: Memory Architecture

```
resources/                    # L1: Raw, immutable, timestamped
├── meetings/                 # Meeting notes and transcripts
└── notes/                    # Standalone notes

.arete/
├── memory/
│   ├── items/                # L2: Atomic facts (extracted, user-approved)
│   │   ├── decisions.md      # Key decisions with rationale
│   │   ├── learnings.md      # Insights from work
│   │   └── agent-observations.md # Your observations about working with user
│   ├── areas/                # L3: Per-area operational snapshot (computed)
│   │   └── {slug}.md         # Active people, open work, topic index, recent decisions
│   ├── topics/               # L3: Per-topic encyclopedic wiki (computed, LLM-synthesized)
│   │   └── {slug}.md         # Current state, why/background, scope, open questions, source trail
│   ├── summaries/            # L3: Free-form synthesized context (collaboration, sessions)
│   │   ├── collaboration.md  # How to work with user (derived from observations)
│   │   └── sessions.md       # Work session tracking
│   ├── index.md              # Catalog of topic + person + area pages (Obsidian landing)
│   ├── log.md                # Append-only audit of ingest/refresh/lint events
│   └── archive/              # Compacted old L2 entries
└── activity/
    └── activity-log.md       # Chronological activity record

now/scratchpad.md             # Shared working space (user + agent)
```

### L3 has three flavors

L3 is not one thing — three surfaces with distinct roles:

- **Area memory** (`areas/{slug}.md`) — operational snapshot per work domain. Who's active, what's open, which topics live here. Thin navigation index, not knowledge synthesis.
- **Topic memory** (`topics/{slug}.md`) — encyclopedic wiki per topic. LLM-synthesized narrative that accumulates on every meeting ingest via `integrateSource`. The boot-context substrate: CLAUDE.md's Active Topics section pulls from here.
- **Summaries** (`summaries/`) — free-form synthesized context (collaboration profile, session log). Authored during /guide sessions.

### Area Memory (L3 — Computed)

Area memory files are **computed views**, not manually maintained. Auto-generated by `arete memory refresh` from area definitions + commitments + decisions + meeting scan + topic enrichment. Do not edit manually.

### Topic Memory (L3 — Computed, LLM-synthesized)

Topic pages at `.arete/memory/topics/{slug}.md` are **materialized from meeting ingestion**. Every time `arete meeting apply` runs, the extracted topic slugs bump the alias/merge pass; committed meetings then trigger `integrateSource` which rewrites the touched sections of each topic page via an LLM call. Content-hash idempotency: re-running on the same (topic, meeting) pair is a no-op.

**How topic pages materialize** — three distinct paths:

1. **Live, per meeting** (the primary path). `arete meeting approve <slug>`
   runs Hook 2 after committing staged items: integrates the meeting
   into each tagged topic's page. This is the Karpathy pattern — knowledge
   compounds as meetings arrive, not in weekly batches. `arete meeting
   apply` also runs Hook 1 (alias/merge) to normalize LLM-proposed slugs
   against existing pages so near-duplicates like `cover-whale-email-
   templates` coerce to the existing `cover-whale-templates` canonical.
2. **One-shot backfill** (once per workspace, when you first adopt topic
   memory). `arete topic seed` scans every historical meeting's
   `topics:` frontmatter and creates the full catalog. Content-hash
   idempotency means a second `seed` run is a no-op.
3. **Targeted refresh** (when you want to rebuild a specific page from
   scratch). `arete topic refresh <slug>` — re-integrates all meetings
   tagged with `<slug>` against the existing page.

```bash
# Canonical refresh — runs areas + topics + people + CLAUDE.md + index
arete memory refresh          # full refresh
arete memory refresh --area <slug>  # area-scoped (skips topics + index)

# One-shot backfill (adopt topic memory on an existing workspace)
arete topic seed

# Targeted — existing pages only
arete topic refresh <slug>    # rebuild a single topic
arete topic refresh --all     # rebuild all existing topics from their sources

# Browse + query
arete topic list              # list all topics
arete topic show <slug>       # view a single topic page
arete topic find <query>      # retrieve top-k relevant topics for skills

# Health
arete topic lint              # surface stale, stub, orphan, dangling topics
arete topic lint --fix-dangling  # rewrite dangling [[refs]] to plain text

# Per-meeting escape hatch
arete meeting apply --skip-topics      # skip alias/merge at apply time
arete meeting approve --skip-topics    # skip Hook 2 integration at commit
```

Topic memory is included in `arete search --scope memory` AND `arete topic find --json` for skill context injection. See `topic_page_retrieval` pattern in `PATTERNS.md`.

## Session Start (GUIDE Mode)

At the beginning of each conversation, proactively gather context:

1. **Read recent observations** — `.arete/memory/items/agent-observations.md` (last 5 entries)
   - Look for patterns, preferences, corrections that should inform this session

2. **Check current focus** — `now/week.md` (if exists)
   - What are this week's priorities and goals?

3. **Check open commitments** — Run `arete commitments list`
   - What's owed to others? What are others owed?

This ensures continuity without requiring explicit briefing. If files don't exist, skip gracefully.

